entry.tran: 不可剥夺的;不能让与的
entry.def: If you say that someone has an inalienable right to something, you are emphasizing that they have a right to it which cannot be changed or taken away.

example.ex: He said the republic now had an inalienable right to self-determination.
example.tran: 他说共和国现在拥有不可剥夺的自决权。

example.ex: ...respect for the inalienable rights of peoples and nations.
example.tran: 对各民族、国家不可剥夺权利的尊重
